    "135 In the UK, the Home Office accused tens of thousands of students of cheating in a government-approved English language test based on an automated voice recognition system.",
    "136 For students with invalid test results, the Home Office cancelled their visas and refused any pending applications; others were taken into immigration detention in the UK and subsequently deported.",
    "137 As it was later proven through several audits and expert opinion, the system was riddled with errors and lacked accuracy in generating evidence.",
    "138 The quality of input dataprocessed by the system to generate evidencerepresented a further issue.",
    "If data are not correct, up to date, and relevant, the evidence generated will be inaccurate."
